    public class HierarchicalObjectPropertyDesc
extends ObjectPropertyGround
implements ObjectPropertyExpression.Sub<HierarchicalObjectPropertyDesc>, ObjectPropertyExpression.Super<HierarchicalObjectPropertyDesc>
    This is an example of a 'compound' ObjectProperty Descriptor which implements 2 ObjectPropertyExpression interfaces:
    • ObjectPropertyExpression.Sub: to describe that an ObjectProperty subsumes another ObjectProperty.
    • ObjectPropertyExpression.Super: to describe that an ObjectProperty super-sumes another ObjectProperty.
    See FullObjectPropertyDesc for an example of a 'compound' Individual Descriptor that implements all ObjectPropertyExpressions.

      • writeExpressionAxioms

        public java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> writeExpressionAxioms()
